# Phase 15 Plan: Import Songs

This phase introduces the ability to import songs from the widely used OpenSong format into KeryxPro. 

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Handling Duplicate Titles:** If you import a song with a title that already exists in your KeryxPro database, how should the app handle it? 
> 1. Skip the import of that specific song (keep the existing one).
> 2. Overwrite the existing song with the new import.
> 3. Add it as a new song with a duplicate name (e.g., "Amazing Grace (1)").
> *I will default to option 1 (Skip existing) unless you prefer otherwise.*

> [!NOTE]
> **Where to find OpenSong Databases:** 
> OpenSong is a very popular open-source format. You can find databases and files in several places:
> - **Direct from OpenSong:** You can download the OpenSong app, which comes with some public domain songs, and copy the files from its `Songs` folder.
> - **CCLI SongSelect:** If your church has a SongSelect subscription, you can directly export chord sheets/lyrics into OpenSong format.
> - **Community Forums:** The OpenSong community and OpenLP community forums often share Zip files of public domain worship songs in this format.

